Someone makes an argument against checking malloc, talking about the overhead it adds.<p>Does anyone have a problem with using a malloc wrapper?<p><pre><code>  void *Malloc(size_t size) {
    void *r = malloc(size);

    if(r == NULL)
      /* do things to quit the app */

    return r;
  }
</code></pre>
edit: yay for "  " code blocks.  Hacker News++<p>edit again: I wasn't clear.  I meant overhead in terms of lines of code it added.  I'm asking if it makes sense to wrap it up in a nice upper-case call that just terminates the program if the worst happens.
